Educational Technology for Students






Educational Technology for Students
Students may be required to use educational software and applications, such as Blackboard Learn, VoiceThread, and Respondus, for courses.





            Students Tools
          Heading link



 
Copy link












                            Blackboard Introduction
                    

                Blackboard Learn is the centrally-supported learning management system used by faculty and students at UIC.
            












                            Ally File Transformer
                    

                Enables students to upload a course file and download it in an alternate format.
            












                            Digital Textbooks
                    

                Digital textbooks, or e-books, are a computer rendition of physical textbooks with additional features.
            












                            iClicker
                    

                iClicker is a classroom response system instructors may use in courses to conduct student polls or ask questions.
            












                            Respondus Monitor
                    

                Proctoring tools that may be required for assessments and exams.
            












                            VoiceThread
                    

                An interactive collaboration tool that facilitates asynchronous online discussions.
            












